---
import TrustLayout from '../../layouts/TrustLayout.astro';
const title = 'Terms | Utilitas';
const description = 'The terms, limitations, and responsibilities that apply when using the Utilitas hub and its project links.';
---

<TrustLayout title={title} description={description} path="/terms/" eyebrow="Trust centre">
  <h2>Using this website</h2>
  <p>You may browse the Utilitas hub and follow its project links for lawful purposes. Do not interfere with the site, bypass access controls, misrepresent the project, or use automated traffic in a way that degrades access for others.</p>

  <h2>Information, not professional advice</h2>
  <p>Descriptions on this hub are general product information. They are not engineering, construction, legal, medical, financial, privacy, or security advice. Individual tools may produce estimates or reports, and their own terms describe the assumptions and limits that apply.</p>

  <h2>Availability and changes</h2>
  <p>Projects may be revised, paused, renamed, or removed. Work labelled in development may change before launch and should not be treated as a promised release date or final specification. A production link is shown only after that destination is ready to be represented as live.</p>

  <h2>External destinations</h2>
  <p>SVG Vector Lab and future project sites keep separate origins and policies. When you leave Utilitas, the destination's terms, privacy disclosures, and technical behaviour apply. The hub is not responsible for unrelated third-party content reached through further links.</p>

  <h2>Advertising</h2>
  <p>The hub may display advertising provided by Google. Advertising does not constitute an endorsement, and advertisers do not control Utilitas editorial content. Do not treat an advertisement as part of a project interface or as professional advice.</p>

  <h2>Disclaimer</h2>
  <p>The hub is provided on an as-available basis without warranties of uninterrupted operation, fitness for a particular purpose, or error-free content to the extent permitted by applicable law. You remain responsible for verifying information and keeping backups appropriate to your use.</p>

  <h2>Questions</h2>
  <p>Use the <a href="/contact/">contact page</a> for questions about these terms and identify the specific page or project involved.</p>
</TrustLayout>
